axis: one-shot-violation-diagnostic
status: pending-runtime
needs: one-shot vs multi-shot tracking + a typed diagnostic on violation
measured: resuming twice from a handler over a plain (non-`multi`) `effect` runs
  silently and returns a value (`resume(1) + resume(2)` → `3`) on BOTH portable-VM
  tiers — `ssc run` (interp) and `ssc run --bytecode` (2026-07-14) — a one-shot
  violation is NOT diagnosed; only the `multi` keyword is advisory, not enforced.
  Cross-lane (codex-interop audit): the guard is present in the v1 interpreter / JS
  paths and absent in generated JVM; confirmed absent on the portable-VM native lane.
  Tracked: BUGS.md `control-interop-portable-vm-oneshot-guard-absent`.
expected: an effect declared one-shot that is resumed more than once yields a
  deterministic typed diagnostic, not a silent multi-shot (§14.1 "one-shot
  violations"; core: "encoding a one-shot frame never yields the reusable type").
